originalText.text: We had a very memorable family dinning experience here.  The staff at every touch point was very courteous and attentive.  We were seated at the back of a dimly lit and very ambient dinning room.  The other patrons seemed all very immersed in their experiences as well.  That added to the overall welcoming atmosphere.  Our seating was a little too low for the height of the table but we quickly got used to it.   I sampled everything from a well crafted family style prix fixe menu. The appetizers were my favorites.  Each one was delectable. The entrees were delightful as well.  However, I found the honey and caramel sauces on some of the dishes were a little overpowering.  Of the desserts, the carrot cake caught my attention…moist and velvety and not too sweet. There was a photographer with a very keen eye who captured some amazing shots to immortalize the moments…for a prize of course.  But they were worth it.  I would definitely come back and next time spend some time at the bar too.  Highly recommend.

originalText.text: Had a birthday celebration for my son’s girlfriend birthday at this Asian restaurant. We had a private room for 20 people. We had reservation for 7p -9p and we were running late due to weekend, holiday time. We got there around 7:30p and they were nice enough to extended from 7:30p to 9:30p. Place was packed. Room was cozy for your private time. . Head waiter Alexy was very friendly and courteous and attentive.  Food was very good and tasty. It was family style menu. One thing though food portion could have been a bit more for 100$ per person. Between the appetizers and entrees I was full.

originalText.text: First time dining at Sei Less and was pleasantly surprised by the ambiance and vibe. A lot more spacious than user photos show. Our waiter, Carlos was beyond amazing and very attentive, read us the nights dinner specials and gave us suggestions from the cocktail menu. Food came out fairly quick, piping hot and the portions were generous. Good presentation and delicious meal. We did not want to over indulge and were going to an event nearby after dinner and wanted to be doggy bag free. Great atmosphere, inquired about the availability of the valet parking and will definitely be dining here again one day. Shhhhhhhh....Sei Less!

originalText.text: Everything here was great! I had the Sei Less Lobster Noodles as my entree. For appetizers, we shared the pan fried Chicken Dumplings, Lobster Spring Rolls, & Short Rib Bao Buns. The Do More, Sei Less cocktail was great as well. The service was exceptional! I'll definitely be back!

originalText.text: Everyone from the hostess to the servers and staff were really nice, friendly and accommodating. I really enjoyed my food we had a lot of things so I won't mention them all but the highlights for me were the lobster soup spoons  the bok choy and the beef entree. The definitely not were the Kung Pao chicken entree and the crab cake appetizer. But overall the food was really good my drink with delicious and cute but before I finish it someone took a way because they're very diligent about turning over the table and keeping it clean and giving you fresh plates and utensils which I really liked. My server also just got me a new drink and it worked out fine.
